The term “Computer Aided Manufacturing” (CAM) congers up different ideas in the minds of different people, depending upon their particular area of expertise, and the size and type of the company they are associated with. It ranges from those types of activites such as Material Requirements Planning, Inventory Management, Factory Capacity Planning, Shop Floor Control etc. to such activities as routing and placement of components on printed wiring cards as well as the art work generation. Another idea of 'CAM' is the actual operation and control of process equipment as well as production test equipment. Some feel that CAM is all of these things together. This paper deals with the actual operation and control of process and test equipment on the factory floor.